Break 1 of the cookies into four pieces; reserve for garnish. Crush remaining 7 cookies; set aside. Pour milk into medium bowl. Add dry pudding mix; beat with wire whisk 2 min. or until well blended. Stir in crushed cookies. Gently stir in 1/2 cup of the whipped topping. Spoon evenly into four dessert bowls. Top with remaining 1/4 cup whipped topping and the reserved cookie pieces. Store leftover dessert in refrigerator.